quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Switch[/h1]

Consider the following example, which displays the appropriate message for each day. [code format="php" codeId="482"]$today = 'Tue';

[b]switch [/b]($today) {
  [b]case [/b]"Mon":
    echo "Today is Monday.";
    [b]break[/b];
  [b]case [/b]"Tue":
    echo "Today is Tuesday.";
    [b]break[/b];
  [b]case [/b]"Wed":
    echo "Today is Wednesday.";
    [b]break[/b];
  [b]case [/b]"Thu":
    echo "Today is Thursday.";
    [b]break[/b];
  [b]case [/b]"Fri":
     echo "Today is Friday.";
     [b]break[/b];
  [b]case [/b]"Sat":
     echo "Today is Saturday.";
     [b]break[/b];
  [b]case [/b]"Sun":
     echo "Today is Sunday.";
     [b]break[/b];
  [b]default[/b]:
     echo "Invalid day.";
}
//Outputs "Today is Tuesday."[/code]
[note]The [b]break[/b] keyword that follows each case is used to keep the code from automatically running into the next case. If you forget the [b]break;[/b] statement, PHP will automatically continue through the next case statements, even when the case doesn't match.[/note]

[h1]default[/h1]

The [b]default [/b]statement is used if no match is found. [code format="php" codeId="483"]$x=5;
switch ($x) {
  case 1:
    echo "One";
    break;
  case 2:
    echo "Two";
    break;
  [b]default:
    [/b]echo "No match";
}

//Outputs "No match"[/code] 
[note]The [b]default[/b] statement is optional, so it can be omitted.[/note]

quizzes.question:
What output results from the following code?
$mo = "December";
switch ($mo) {
case "July":
    echo "Summer";
break;
case "January":
case "February":
    echo "Winter";
}
?>

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Switch[/h1]

Failing to specify the [b]break[/b] statement causes PHP to continue to executing the statements that follow the [b]case[/b], until it finds a [b]break[/b]. You can use this behavior if you need to arrive at the same output for more than one case.[code format="php" codeId="484"]$day = 'Wed';

[b]switch [/b]($day) {
[b]  case [/b]'Mon':
    echo 'First day of the week';
[b]    break[/b];
[b]  case [/b]'Tue':
[b]  case [/b]'Wed':
[b]  case [/b]'Thu':
    echo 'Working day';
[b]    break[/b];
[b]  case [/b]'Fri':
    echo 'Friday!';
[b]    break[/b];
[b]  default[/b]:
    echo 'Weekend!';
}

//Outputs "Working day"[/code]
[note]The example above will have the same output if[b] $day[/b] equals 'Tue', 'Wed', or 'Thu'. [/note]
